Looking at this problem, I need to show that `|RiemannSum (f n) a b M - RiemannSum F a b M| < ε` given that `∀ (x : ℝ), |f n x - F x| < ε / (b - a)`.

The key insight is that the Riemann sum difference can be bounded using the uniform bound on function values. The Riemann sum is a sum over intervals of width `(b-a)/M`, and the difference at each point is bounded by `ε/(b-a)`, so the total difference is bounded by `ε`.

```lean
  have h := RiemannSum_diff_bound (f n) F a b M hab hN
  calc |RiemannSum (f n) a b M - RiemannSum F a b M| 
      ≤ (ε / (b - a)) * (b - a) := h
    _ = ε := by field_simp
```
